00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:08.107 align:middle line:84%
Or is it being directed
by the mainstream media

00:10:08.107 --> 00:10:11.569 align:middle line:84%
to divide us along
different fault lines?

00:10:11.569 --> 00:10:13.321 align:middle line:84%
And then the other
question is, are people

00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:14.739 align:middle line:90%
really so divided and angry?

00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:17.450 align:middle line:84%
Or are they just upset
because the economy is sliding

00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:20.203 align:middle line:84%
and we don't really have
the language or the outlets

00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:20.995 align:middle line:90%
to discuss it?

00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:22.455 align:middle line:84%
Like we all know
inflation is real.

00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:24.791 align:middle line:84%
Like it's not Ron
Paul apocalypse real,

00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:27.418 align:middle line:84%
but we know it's real because
things are more expensive.

00:10:27.418 --> 00:10:29.045 align:middle line:84%
And we don't have
the framework to talk

00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:30.463 align:middle line:90%
to each other about this.

00:10:30.463 --> 00:10:32.423 align:middle line:84%
And we know that the jobs
are not good anymore,

00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:35.426 align:middle line:84%
because people who are 50 are
Ubering, whereas they used

00:10:35.426 --> 00:10:37.262 align:middle line:90%
to have a pension or something.

00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:39.722 align:middle line:84%
They worked at the factory,
and then they have a pension,

00:10:39.722 --> 00:10:41.140 align:middle line:90%
and they're taken care of.

00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:43.434 align:middle line:90%
Nobody is taken care of anymore.

00:10:43.434 --> 00:10:45.478 align:middle line:84%
And so there is
definitely division.

00:10:45.478 --> 00:10:49.440 align:middle line:84%
But my question is, is it
basically economic unease

00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.276 align:middle line:84%
that the elites are
able to redirect

00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:52.402 align:middle line:90%
into certain narratives?

00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:54.112 align:middle line:84%
Or is this just a
divided country?

00:10:54.112 --> 00:10:55.822 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:10:55.822 --> 00:10:58.074 align:middle line:84%
>> SEAN: Going into this
issue of the elites creating

00:10:58.074 --> 00:11:01.870 align:middle line:84%
a narrative, the Nixon
administration used fake news

00:11:01.870 --> 00:11:04.831 align:middle line:84%
to create the war on
drugs, if I'm correct.

00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:06.291 align:middle line:84%
Describe that
history a little bit.

00:11:06.291 --> 00:11:08.209 align:middle line:84%
>> SEAMAN: I'm not an
expert on the Nixon era,

00:11:08.209 --> 00:11:11.337 align:middle line:84%
but my understanding was that
there were really two pushes

00:11:11.337 --> 00:11:12.714 align:middle line:90%
to criminalize cannabis.

00:11:12.714 --> 00:11:16.843 align:middle line:84%
And the first was in the '30s,
and it was primarily racist.

00:11:16.843 --> 00:11:19.470 align:middle line:84%
But it was also being
driven by industry.

00:11:19.470 --> 00:11:22.515 align:middle line:84%
There were concerns that hemp
was pushing out cotton mills

00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:23.850 align:middle line:90%
and all of this stuff.

00:11:23.850 --> 00:11:26.436 align:middle line:84%
Hemp was in many ways
a superior product,

00:11:26.436 --> 00:11:29.188 align:middle line:84%
so the people not pushing
that product obviously

00:11:29.188 --> 00:11:30.523 align:middle line:90%
wanted to get rid of it.

00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:32.191 align:middle line:90%
That was the first wave.

00:11:32.191 --> 00:11:36.029 align:middle line:84%
And the second wave that
really sealed the nail

00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:40.199 align:middle line:84%
in the coffin of cannabis use
in the United States was Nixon.

00:11:40.199 --> 00:11:42.952 align:middle line:84%
And my understanding was
that some of his advisers

00:11:42.952 --> 00:11:43.870 align:middle line:90%
were looking around.

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:46.706 align:middle line:84%
There's widespread dissent
to the war in Vietnam--

00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:48.290 align:middle line:90%
not a popular war.

00:11:48.290 --> 00:11:51.586 align:middle line:84%
More and more Americans were
dropping their support for it.

00:11:51.586 --> 00:11:53.046 align:middle line:84%
And some of his
advisers go, look,

00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:56.841 align:middle line:84%
we can't put people in prison
for violations for protesting,

00:11:56.841 --> 00:11:58.843 align:middle line:84%
because that's protected
by the First Amendment.

00:11:58.843 --> 00:11:59.969 align:middle line:90%
That's not illegal.

00:11:59.969 --> 00:12:03.640 align:middle line:84%
But all these people happen to
have cannabis joints on them.

00:12:03.640 --> 00:12:06.893 align:middle line:84%
If we can whip up a frenzy
and get this criminalized,

00:12:06.893 --> 00:12:09.562 align:middle line:84%
all the protesters disappear
because they either

00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.272 align:middle line:84%
don't want to be seen
in public, or we're

00:12:11.272 --> 00:12:12.941 align:middle line:90%
going to put them in prison.

00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:14.442 align:middle line:90%
And I believe that was enacted.

00:12:14.442 --> 00:12:16.069 align:middle line:84%
And I think, to an
extent, we're still

00:12:16.069 --> 00:12:19.614 align:middle line:84%
living with the poor decisions
of the Nixon administration.

00:12:19.614 --> 00:12:22.492 align:middle line:84%
I had an MD recently who
thought I was off the wall

00:12:22.492 --> 00:12:24.911 align:middle line:90%
about my pro-cannabis stuff.

00:12:24.911 --> 00:12:26.579 align:middle line:84%
And then he started
looking through some

00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:28.831 align:middle line:84%
