00:12:28.831 --> 00:12:31.834 align:middle line:84%
and some of the continuing
education classes for MDs.

00:12:31.834 --> 00:12:33.419 align:middle line:84%
And he was saying
to me, my god, we've

00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:35.338 align:middle line:84%
really been misled, like
people should not have

00:12:35.338 --> 00:12:36.714 align:middle line:90%
been going to prison for this.

00:12:36.714 --> 00:12:39.592 align:middle line:84%
The biopharmacology of
this thing is crazy.

00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:40.635 align:middle line:90%
It's good for depression.

00:12:40.635 --> 00:12:41.970 align:middle line:90%
It's good for IBS.

00:12:41.970 --> 00:12:43.221 align:middle line:90%
It's good for arthritis pain.

00:12:43.221 --> 00:12:44.389 align:middle line:90%
He's listing all this stuff.

00:12:44.389 --> 00:12:46.140 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, look, I know.

00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:46.975 align:middle line:90%
I live in Colorado.

00:12:46.975 --> 00:12:48.267 align:middle line:90%
I know there's something to it.

00:12:48.267 --> 00:12:49.227 align:middle line:90%
So yeah.

00:12:49.227 --> 00:12:50.061 align:middle line:90%
>> SEAN: Absolutely.

00:12:50.061 --> 00:12:52.313 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you mentioned,
obviously, some of the benefits

00:12:52.313 --> 00:12:54.941 align:middle line:84%
aside from the medicinal
purposes for smoking marijuana,

00:12:54.941 --> 00:12:59.737 align:middle line:84%
but hemp itself is used for
cloth and clothing, for paper.

00:12:59.737 --> 00:13:02.073 align:middle line:84%
Obviously it's a
wonderful plant.

00:13:02.073 --> 00:13:05.034 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that it's been
so demonized throughout--

00:13:05.034 --> 00:13:06.411 align:middle line:84%
>> SEAMAN: Well,
that's the thing.

00:13:06.411 --> 00:13:07.370 align:middle line:90%
It is a plant.

00:13:07.370 --> 00:13:11.082 align:middle line:84%
And somehow it made its way
from plant to Schedule 1 drug,

00:13:11.082 --> 00:13:14.419 align:middle line:84%
