00:13:46.367 --> 00:13:49.495 align:middle line:84%
I genuinely believe that it's
a spiritual practice when

00:13:49.495 --> 00:13:50.955 align:middle line:90%
a person gets high.

00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:55.752 align:middle line:84%
And in Genesis of the Bible,
the Judeo-Christian God

00:13:55.752 --> 00:13:59.756 align:middle line:84%
says that you have access
to every seed-bearing plant.

00:13:59.756 --> 00:14:03.051 align:middle line:84%
Well, cannabis sativa is
not an exception from that.

00:14:03.051 --> 00:14:04.635 align:middle line:90%
It's a seed-bearing plant.

00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:07.263 align:middle line:84%
And it was found naturally
throughout North America.

00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:09.891 align:middle line:84%
So why would that one be
one that God doesn't like?

00:14:09.891 --> 00:14:11.809 align:middle line:84%
Why would that one be
one that's off limits?

00:14:11.809 --> 00:14:13.478 align:middle line:90%
Of course, God doesn't care.

00:14:13.478 --> 00:14:14.896 align:middle line:90%
It's Nixon that didn't like it.

00:14:14.896 --> 00:14:16.731 align:middle line:90%
And we know now why.

00:14:16.731 --> 00:14:19.067 align:middle line:84%
So we need to correct
course there, I think.

00:14:19.067 --> 00:14:20.777 align:middle line:84%
And, yeah, it is a
spiritual experience.

00:14:20.777 --> 00:14:24.322 align:middle line:84%
I think whenever you
get outside of sober--

00:14:24.322 --> 00:14:26.199 align:middle line:90%
