certain drugs, whether it

00:15:15.581 --> 00:15:18.793 align:middle line:84%
be cocaine or heroin or
the more hardcore drugs,

00:15:18.793 --> 00:15:20.545 align:middle line:84%
is that they basically
have deviated

00:15:20.545 --> 00:15:23.923 align:middle line:84%
from the original plant and the
original purpose of it, which

00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:26.467 align:middle line:84%
was not just for recreation
and fun and partying,

00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:28.094 align:middle line:84%
but actually to
have an awakening

00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:30.471 align:middle line:90%
and a raising of consciousness.

00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:32.515 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that we're
going to potentially see,

00:15:32.515 --> 00:15:36.561 align:middle line:84%
because of the legalization
of marijuana in states

00:15:36.561 --> 00:15:39.647 align:middle line:84%
like Colorado and Washington
and now California,

00:15:39.647 --> 00:15:42.441 align:middle line:84%
that it's really just going
to boom, that ultimately we're

00:15:42.441 --> 00:15:44.485 align:middle line:84%
going to see America
transformed in the next four

00:15:44.485 --> 00:15:46.279 align:middle line:84%
to eight years, let's
say, and legalization

00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:47.363 align:middle line:90%
across the country?

00:15:47.363 --> 00:15:49.157 align:middle line:84%
>> SEAMAN: I think
we're already seeing it.

00:15:49.157 --> 00:15:51.534 align:middle line:84%
